00:21:23.980 --> 00:21:25.100
And why is that?

00:21:25.100 --> 00:21:28.220
Because between revenue and net
income, you have-- this

00:21:28.220 --> 00:21:30.130
pointer probably doesn't work
very well-- but you have lots

00:21:30.130 --> 00:21:34.440
of line items that management
can utilize to derive whatever

00:21:34.440 --> 00:21:35.670
net income they want.

00:21:35.670 --> 00:21:37.840
So revenue is the
most important.

00:21:37.840 --> 00:21:40.390
To the extent that I have
concerns about a company,

00:21:40.390 --> 00:21:43.080
they're in direct proportion
to where they reside on the

00:21:43.080 --> 00:21:44.460
income statement.

00:21:44.460 --> 00:21:46.430
In an extreme case, if the
revenue for a company were

00:21:46.430 --> 00:21:49.730
fictitious, which may be the
case with Autonomy, that

00:21:49.730 --> 00:21:50.850
Hewlett Packard acquired--

00:21:50.850 --> 00:21:52.080
we're really going to rag on

00:21:52.080 --> 00:21:54.100
Hewlett-Packard today, I think--

00:21:54.100 --> 00:21:56.120
then the entire financial model
would be fictitious.

00:21:56.120 --> 00:21:58.140
So why does it matter what the
earnings are if the revenue is

00:21:58.140 --> 00:21:59.730
not even real?

00:21:59.730 --> 00:22:01.550
So when you're analyzing a
company, you want to look from

00:22:01.550 --> 00:22:02.930
the top down.

00:22:02.930 --> 00:22:06.190
The net income number is the
first line item on the

00:22:06.190 --> 00:22:09.080
operating cash flow statement,
so when you analyze cash flow,

00:22:09.080 --> 00:22:13.570
if the net income happens to be
manipulated, then cash flow

00:22:13.570 --> 00:22:16.000
quality's probably
low as well.

00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:18.880
But the vertical depiction of
an income statement really

00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:23.800
kind of helps show the way that
we think about things.

00:22:23.800 --> 00:22:26.820
So revenue related issues,
