01:15:11.220 --> 01:15:12.910
Fashion Island or something.

01:15:12.910 --> 01:15:17.130
The big fancy mall
down in Irvine.

01:15:17.130 --> 01:15:20.800
He goes to these neighborhood
strip malls anchored by a

01:15:20.800 --> 01:15:26.105
supermarket, where there's no
competition, and somebody gave

01:15:26.105 --> 01:15:30.130
him $400 million and
said, OK, Stuart.

01:15:30.130 --> 01:15:32.790
Go out and buy these
in the crash.

01:15:32.790 --> 01:15:35.250
And he knew all the players
because he's been doing this

01:15:35.250 --> 01:15:36.550
for 40 years.

01:15:36.550 --> 01:15:39.610
So all these people
were underwater.

01:15:39.610 --> 01:15:40.420
They call him up.

01:15:40.420 --> 01:15:42.270
These things aren't
even advertised.

01:15:42.270 --> 01:15:46.930
And he's taking them for the
note that they owe the bank.

01:15:46.930 --> 01:15:49.300
They just want to hand
over the keys.

01:15:49.300 --> 01:15:53.430
And it's pretty hard to lose
money when you invest at that

01:15:53.430 --> 01:15:57.940
point, because people in
neighborhoods, which don't

01:15:57.940 --> 01:16:00.730
have other shopping options,
are going to go to the

01:16:00.730 --> 01:16:01.820
supermarket.

01:16:01.820 --> 01:16:04.710
He fixes the parking lot, puts
some trees up, puts a new coat

01:16:04.710 --> 01:16:08.840
of paint on, has escalator
[? rents, ?] fills up the

01:16:08.840 --> 01:16:10.260
empty spaces with anything.

01:16:13.300 --> 01:16:17.720
I mean, not just nail salons
or tattoo parlors.

01:16:17.720 --> 01:16:20.040
Just to make a little
joke there.

01:16:20.040 --> 01:16:24.050
But I can see the cash flows
from that, and I can see the

01:16:24.050 --> 01:16:25.240
distressed real estate.

01:16:25.240 --> 01:16:28.110
That's one of my favorite,
favorite areas because I can

01:16:28.110 --> 01:16:29.090
value the cash flows.

01:16:29.090 --> 01:16:32.380
Residential, it's just too--

01:16:32.380 --> 01:16:34.870
local, local, local.

